Struggling with Kubernetes Networking? Let’s simplify !
Ingress vs ingress controller vs load balancer
These 3 components work together to handle traffic in Kubernetes 👇
🔹 Load Balancer = Entry Gate 🚪
👉 Brings external traffic into the cluster
👉 Distributes requests across services
👉 Ensures high availability
🔹 Ingress = Smart Router 🧭
👉 Defines where the request should go
👉 Supports path & domain-based routing
👉 Example:
/api → backend
/web → frontend
🔹 Ingress Controller = Traffic Manager 🚦
👉 Executes Ingress rules
👉 Routes traffic to the correct service
👉 Runs inside the cluster
🔥 How everything works together:
User → Load Balancer → Ingress Controller → Service → Pods
💡 Remember this simple logic:
Load Balancer = Entry
Ingress = Rules
Ingress Controller = Execution
🎯 Why this matters?
✔️ One entry point for multiple apps
✔️ Cost-efficient (no need for multiple load balancers)
✔️ Scalable & production-ready architecture
